  "school": "ICT",
  "asset": "CL1! (Light Crude Oil Futures)",
  "timeframe": "15-minute with 5-minute entry",
  "market_context": "Oil trading within an established intraday range with a defined range high and range low. London session made a high but failed to displace, simply consolidating inside the range without reaching a significant HTF level before the New York session.",
  "key_observation": "New York manipulated the range low by sweeping below it, aligning with midnight opening price. After initial failure, price closed over the down-close candles forming a change in state of delivery, with the order block sitting in the discount half of the range.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Observed London made a high but did not reach an important level, just consolidated inside the visible range bounded by range high and range low.",
    "Step 2: Marked the range high and range low as the key reference structure for the day.",
    "Step 3: Entered the New York session and watched price sweep below the prior range low, also tagging the midnight opening price area.",
    "Step 4: Dropped down to the 5-minute chart to look for a change in state of delivery; noted price initially failed to close over the down-close candle series.",
    "Step 5: Identified the eventual close over the down-close candles, confirming the change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 6: Considered premium/discount of the range and chose the mean threshold of the bullish order block (sitting in discount) over the opening price for a tighter, higher-probability entry.",
    "Step 7: Placed stop below the swept low (with failure swings on the opposite side acting as draw on liquidity), targeting the opposite side of the range."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price retraced into the discount order block mean threshold and then expanded higher toward the opposite side of the range, validating the long entry.",
  "lessons": "When London fails to reach a key level and only consolidates, expect New York to manipulate the range. After a sweep and CISD, prefer the mean threshold of the order block in discount over the opening price for a higher R:R entry.",
